contracts.name: L1CrossDomainMessenger
contracts.description: Sends messages from host chain to this chain, and relays messages back onto host chain. In the event that a message sent from host chain to this chain is rejected for exceeding this chain's epoch gas limit, it can be resubmitted via this contract's replay function.

directlyReceivedPermissions.description: upgrading the bridge implementation can give access to all funds escrowed therein.

contracts.name: DisputeGameFactory
contracts.description: The dispute game factory allows the creation of dispute games, used to propose state roots and eventually challenge them.

contracts.name: SP1VerifierGateway
contracts.description: This contract is the router for the bridge proofs verification. It stores the mapping between the identifier of the bridge circuit and the address of the onchain verifier contract.

oldVerifier.description: The verifier contract address for SP1, and whether it is frozen (true if frozen). This verifier route was frozen on 2024-09-04.

oldVerifier2.description: The verifier contract address for SP1, and whether it is frozen (true if frozen). This prover route was frozen on 2024-09-21.

oldVerifier3.description: The verifier contract address for SP1, and whether it is frozen (true if frozen). This prover route was frozen on 2024-11-01.

oldVerifier4.description: The verifier contract address for SP1, and whether it is frozen (true if frozen). This prover route was frozen on 2024-11-08.

verifier.description: The prover contract address for SP1, and whether it is frozen (true if frozen).

receivedPermissions.description: it can update the preconfer address, the batch submitter (Sequencer) address and the gas configuration of the system.
upgrading the bridge implementation can give access to all funds escrowed therein.

contracts.name: AddressManager
contracts.description: Legacy contract used to manage a mapping of string names to addresses. Modern OP stack uses a different standard proxy system instead, but this contract is still necessary for backwards compatibility with several older contracts.

contracts.name: L1StandardBridge
contracts.description: The main entry point to deposit ERC20 tokens from host chain to this chain.

via.description: upgrading the bridge implementation can give access to all funds escrowed therein.

contracts.name: DelayedWETH
contracts.description: Contract designed to hold the bonded ETH for each game. It is designed as a wrapper around WETH to allow an owner to function as a backstop if a game would incorrectly distribute funds.

contracts.name: OptimismPortal
contracts.description: The main entry point to deposit funds from host chain to this chain. It also allows to prove and finalize withdrawals.

contracts.name: L1ERC721Bridge
contracts.description: Used to bridge ERC-721 tokens from host chain to this chain.

receivedPermissions.description: holds the power to affect the liveness and safety of the bridge - can transfer ownership, add and freeze verifier routes.

contracts.name: SystemConfig
contracts.description: Contains configuration parameters such as the Sequencer address, gas limit on this chain and the unsafe block signer address.

gasLimit.description: Gas limit for blocks on L2.

contracts.name: SuperchainConfig
contracts.description: This is NOT the shared SuperchainConfig contract of the OP stack Superchain but rather a local fork. It manages the `PAUSED_SLOT`, a boolean value indicating whether the local chain is paused, and `GUARDIAN_SLOT`, the address of the guardian which can pause and unpause the system.

contracts.name: AnchorStateRegistry
contracts.description: Contains the latest confirmed state root that can be used as a starting point in a dispute game.

contracts.name: OptimismMintableERC20Factory
contracts.description: A helper contract that generates OptimismMintableERC20 contracts on the network it's deployed to. OptimismMintableERC20 is a standard extension of the base ERC20 token contract designed to allow the L1StandardBridge contracts to mint and burn tokens. This makes it possible to use an OptimismMintablERC20 as this chain's representation of a token on the host chain, or vice-versa.

directlyReceivedPermissions.description: can verify proofs for the header range [latestBlock, targetBlock] proof.
